      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">A total of 432 registered participants from 11 countries contributed
                to a successful first-ever international symposium devoted exclusively to the topic
                of forensic science error management. Over the three-and-a-half day meeting and
                across 8 technical tracks and 42 sessions, there were 2 keynote and 10 plenary
                speakers, 106 oral presentations, 9 panel discussions, and 18 poster presentations.
                In their keynote address, Brandon Mayfield and Steven Wax, Mr. Mayfield's attorney,
                providing a gripping tale of the impact that an error in a fingerprint "match"
                caused Mr. Mayfield and his family. The symposium concluded with a moot court drama
                and Professor Bill Thompson serving as a "widget identification expert." Science
                magazine (31 July 2015 issue, 349: 462-463) even ran a short summary of the
                symposium.</abstract>
